      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Victim Personal Statement</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">A <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.cps.gov.uk/sites/default/files/documents/legal_guidance/joint-agency-guide-victim-personal-statement_0.pdf">Victim Personal Statement</a> is your opportunity to explain how a crime has affected you, in your own words.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">In England and Wales, you can give a Victim Personal Statement when reporting the crime or later in the process.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">It's separate from your witness statement and helps the court, police, and prosecutors understand the emotional, physical, and financial impact the crime has had on your life.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">The judge may consider your Victim Personal Statement when deciding a sentence. You can also say if you'd like to read it aloud in court.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">Giving a Victim Personal Statement is your choice, and support is available to help you.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">A Victim Personal Statement is sometimes called a Victim Impact Statement.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">For more information contact your local Police Force.</p>
